<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-430-427  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 430 427.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Sept 18 1990 v4 n31 p10(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MapInfo releases data modules for desktop mapping, analysis.andO;(MapInfo Corp. introduces StatInfo demographic, market data files)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Raines.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   MapInfo Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   StatInfo (Data base) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     StatisticsDemographyMarketingData BasesMapsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Raines CohenandM;Troy, N.Y.andP;  -- MapInfo Corp. this week will introduce StatInfo, a series ofdemographic and market data files that can be used with the company's MapInfodesktop mapping application or with standard database programs.andM;Targeted at market researchers, ad planners, government officials and otherswho need to analyze data on a geographical basis, the StatInfo seriesconsists of six modules: StatInfo Population, StatInfo Income, StatInfoRetail, StatInfo Business, StatInfo Summary and StatInfo Canada.andM;Each module contains several types of data.andP;  For example, StatInfo Incomeincludes data on household income from 1980 to 1989, an index of buying powerand a breakdown of households by income level.andP;  The U.S.andP;  modules are brokendown by ZIP codes or counties.andM;The price of modules varies, depending on detail and amount of information.andO;A state's worth of county-bounded data sells for $100; all U.S.andP;  county datain a module is $400; and ZIP code-based information in a category for theentire country goes for $5,500.andM;Shipping now, the files come in .DBF format, the standard used by Ashton-TateCorp.'s dBASE series, Fox Software Inc.'s FoxBASE+/Mac and compatibleproducts.andM;MapInfo Corp. is located at 200 Broadway, Troy, N.Y.andP;  12180; (518) 274-8673;(800) 327-8627.andO;</TEXT></DOC>